Vision

To develop Mongolia into a regional center for heavy equipment engineering, maintenance, and remanufacturing, supporting the mining sector and advancing circular industrial practices.

This system aims to shift Mongolia’s industrial capacity from import dependency toward engineering knowledge, technological capability, and sustainable industrial development.

⸻

Background

Mongolia relies heavily on imported heavy equipment and spare parts for its mining and infrastructure sectors. Maintenance, repair, and component replacement often require long supply chains and high costs.

Developing a domestic engineering and remanufacturing ecosystem would reduce operational costs, create skilled jobs, and build technological capability within the country.

⸻

System Components

1. Heavy Equipment Engineering Center
The engineering center would provide advanced diagnostics, repair, and optimization services for heavy machinery used in mining and construction.

Key capabilities include:
	•	Hydraulic system repair and optimization
	•	Gearbox rebuilding
	•	Electronic diagnostics and control systems
	•	Predictive maintenance technologies

⸻

2. Remanufacturing Facility
A remanufacturing system would recover and restore used mechanical components, extending equipment life cycles and reducing industrial waste.

Typical components include:
	•	Hydraulic pumps
	•	Cylinders
	•	Bearings
	•	Structural mechanical components

This process aligns with the principles of circular economy and industrial sustainability.

⸻

3. Engineering Training and Innovation Center
An education and research center would train Mongolian engineers and technicians in modern industrial technologies.

Focus areas include:
	•	Hydraulic engineering
	•	Industrial automation
	•	Smart maintenance systems
	•	Industrial diagnostics and monitoring

⸻

Strategic Locations

Potential locations for the industrial engineering hub include:
	•	Darkhan – Industrial manufacturing potential
	•	Erdenet – Mining engineering center
	•	Sainshand – Future industrial development zone

⸻

International Partnerships

The system could collaborate with international engineering and technology companies, such as:
	•	Bosch Rexroth
	•	Caterpillar
	•	Komatsu
	•	Hitachi Construction Machinery

⸻

Expected Outcomes
	•	Reduced dependence on imported spare parts
	•	Development of a national engineering ecosystem
	•	Creation of skilled technical jobs
	•	Growth of circular industrial practices

